----

  🚨 Critical Issues Found

  1. JavaScript Bundle: 4.6MB (Target: <500KB)

  - 97% of total page weight
  - Takes 1.27 seconds just to load JS
  - 10-20x larger than best practices

  2. Firestore Listeners Blocking Page Load

  - Pages never reach "networkidle" state
  - Continuous connections to Firestore prevent completion
  - All authenticated pages timeout (30-120 seconds)

  3. Running in Development Mode

  - Development bundles are 2-3x larger than production
  - Hot Module Replacement adding overhead

  ✅ What's Working Well

  - Fast server response (23.5ms TTFB) ✓
  - No JavaScript errors ✓
  - Authentication functional ✓
  - Lundies theme colors applied correctly ✓

  🎯 Immediate Actions (Do Now)

  1. Build production bundle:
  pnpm run build && pnpm start
  This alone will reduce bundle size by 50-70%.

  2. Use Firebase Lite SDK:
  Check src/lib/firebase.ts - switch to modular imports and use lite
  versions for non-realtime queries.

  3. Audit Firestore listeners:
  Replace onSnapshot() with getDocs() for static data. Only use real-time
   listeners where truly needed (booking availability, live updates).

  4. Enable code splitting:
  Split admin routes from guest routes so users don't download
  unnecessary code.

  📊 Performance Budget

  | Metric    | Current  | Target |
  |-----------|----------|--------|
  | JS Bundle | 4.6MB ⚠️ | 300KB  |
  | Page Load | >30s ⚠️  | <3s    |
  | FCP       | 664ms ✓  | <1s    |

